  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq" id="faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-tag">Common questions</div>
        <h2>Things schools ask before signing on.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            <span>What file formats does Acumen support?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10"/></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">.xlsx and .xls files up to 10MB. Acumen handles both comprehensive multi-sheet Cambridge files (component scores and raw marks) and summary single-sheet provisional files with final grades only.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            <span>What counts as one upload?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10"/></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">One upload equals one result file. A typical school uploads 2–4 files per academic year — June IGCSE, November IGCSE, June A Level, and November A Level. Credits never expire, so you can use them across multiple years.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            <span>Can multiple staff members use one account?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10"/></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">Yes. Acumen supports multiple user accounts within a single school account. You can create logins for academic directors, heads of department, and data managers — all with access to the same analytics.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            <span>How is my data stored and protected?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10"/></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">All data is stored in an encrypted PostgreSQL database. Files are processed server-side and the temporary upload is deleted immediately after parsing. Sessions are secured with encrypted tokens and a 7-day TTL.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            <span>Does Acumen support exam boards beyond Cambridge?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10"/></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">Currently no. Acumen is purpose-built for Cambridge International Education (CIE) result files. Support for other examination boards is on our roadmap based on demand.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            <span>Can I import historical data?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10"/></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">Yes. Acumen supports uploads from 2010 onward, allowing you to build a full historical picture of school performance, track long-term trends, and compare cohorts across many exam sessions.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

